@startuml
title UC10 - View Profile / History Sequence
actor User
actor Admin
participant "Web UI\n(ProfilePage / HistoryPage)" as UI
participant "Profile API\n(/profile/*)" as API
participant "Admin Users API\n(/admin/users/:id/*)" as AdminAPI
participant "ProfileService" as Svc
participant "ProfileRepository" as Repo
participant "LeaderboardRepository" as LbRepo
database "DB" as DB

User -> UI : Open /profile
UI -> API : GET /profile/me (Bearer token)
API -> Svc : getMyProfile(userId)
Svc -> Repo : findUser(userId) + getStats(userId)
Svc -> LbRepo : findUserRank(userId, month, year)
Repo -> DB : query User, MatchParticipation, Prediction
LbRepo -> DB : query monthly wins/accuracy/streak
DB --> Repo : rows
DB --> LbRepo : rank row
Repo --> Svc : user + stats
LbRepo --> Svc : monthlyRank | null
Svc --> API : ProfileResponse
API --> UI : 200 OK

User -> UI : Open /history (page N)
UI -> API : GET /profile/history?page=N
API -> Svc : getMyHistory(userId, query)
Svc -> Repo : listHistory(userId, skip, take)
Repo -> DB : query MatchParticipation + Match + Team
DB --> Repo : rows + total
Repo --> Svc : items + total
Svc --> API : HistoryResponse
API --> UI : 200 OK

Admin -> UI : Open user detail (support)
UI -> AdminAPI : GET /admin/users/:id/profile | /history
AdminAPI -> Svc : getMyProfile(id) | getMyHistory(id, query)
note right of AdminAPI : requireRole('ADMIN') guards this route
Svc --> AdminAPI : same response shape as self-service
AdminAPI --> UI : 200 OK
@enduml
